edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.util
Class PartNameTools

java.lang.Object
  edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.util.PartNameTools

public class PartNameTools
extends java.lang.Object

This class is to aid manipulating and converting Xilinx part names and the FamilyType enum. It has facilities to convert part names to its corresponding family type as well as many other methods.

Author:
Chris Lavin Created on: Jan 27, 2011

isFamilyTypeLegacy

public static boolean isFamilyTypeLegacy(FamilyType familyType)
This method determines which family types require the older version of the Xilinx tools (10.1.03 or older).

Parameters:
familyType - The family type to check.
Returns:
True if this part requires older tools (10.1.03) or older, false otherwise.

removeSpeedGrade

public static java.lang.String removeSpeedGrade(java.lang.String partName)
This method removes the speed grade (ex: -10) from a conventional Xilinx part name.

Parameters:
partName - The name of the part to remove the speed grade from.
Returns:
The base part name with speed grade removed. If no speed grade is present, returns the original string.

getFamilyTypeFromPart

public static FamilyType getFamilyTypeFromPart(java.lang.String partName)
This method will take a Xilinx part name and determine its base family architecture name. Ex: xq4vlx100 will return VIRTEX4. For differentiating family types (qvirtex4 rather than virtex4) use getExactFamilyTypeFromPart().

Parameters:
partName - Name of the part
Returns:
The base family architecture type or null if invalid partName.

splitPartName

private static java.lang.String[] splitPartName(java.lang.String partName)
This helper method will parse a part name into smaller parts which are alternating letters and numbers. For example: xc5vlx110tff1136 becomes ['xc', '5', 'vlx', '110', 'tff', '1136']

Parameters:
partName - Part name to parse.
Returns:
The parts of the part name

getExactFamilyTypeFromPart

public static FamilyType getExactFamilyTypeFromPart(java.lang.String partName)
Gets and returns the exact Xilinx family type of the part name (ex: qvirtex4 instead of virtex4). DO NOT use exact family methods if it is to be used for accessing device or wire enumeration files as RapidSmith does not generate files for devices that have XDLRC compatible files.

Returns:
The exact Xilinx family type from the given part name.

getFamilyTypeFromFamilyName

public static FamilyType getFamilyTypeFromFamilyName(java.lang.String name)
This method will take a string of a family name and return a family type.

Parameters:
name - The given family name.
Returns:
The family type or null if the string name is an invalid family name.

getBaseTypeFromFamilyType

public static FamilyType getBaseTypeFromFamilyType(FamilyType type)
This method will take a familyType and return the base familyType architecture. For example, the XDLRC RapidSmith uses for Automotive Spartan 6, Low Power Spartan 6 and Military Grade Spartan 6 all have the same base architecture: Spartan 6. This method determines the base architecture based on the familyType.

Parameters:
type - The given family type.
Returns:
The base family type architecture.

getExactFamilyNameFromPart

public static java.lang.String getExactFamilyNameFromPart(java.lang.String partName)
Gets and returns the all lower case exact Xilinx family name of the part name (ex: qvirtex4 instead of virtex4). DO NOT use exact family methods if it is to be used for accessing device or wire enumeration files as RapidSmith does not generate files for devices that have XDLRC compatible files.

Returns:
The exact Xilinx family name of the part name.

getFamilyNameFromPart

public static java.lang.String getFamilyNameFromPart(java.lang.String partName)
Gets and returns the all lower case base family name of the part name. This ensures compatibility with all RapidSmith files. For differentiating family names (qvirtex4 rather than virtex4) use getExactFamilyName().

Returns:
The base family name of the given part name.

This method will return the formal family name as given by Xilinx 'partgen.'

Parameters:
type - Type of family to get formal name.
Returns:
The formal family name or null if none exists.
